# Fluff Date: 2026-02-21 18:24:59
overview:<p>The Redback is one of the rare BattleMech designs produced by the ill-fated Clan Widowmaker during the early years of Clan society. Based on the Star League-era Maelstrom chassis that the SLDF had taken with them on the Exodus, the Redback emerged around 2828 as Widowmaker scientists sought to improve upon the original design using newly developed Clan technologies. The 'Mech proved popular with Widowmaker MechWarriors in the years following Operation Klondike, serving as a capable front-line brawler that blended proven Star League engineering with experimental Clan weaponry. As a mixed-technology design incorporating both SLDF surplus components and prototype Clan systems, the Redback stands as a fascinating snapshot of the transitional period between the fall of the Star League and the full maturation of Clan military technology.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Redback retains the seventy-five-ton mass and general configuration of its Maelstrom ancestor, maintaining the same 5/8 movement profile that gives the heavy 'Mech respectable speed for its weight class. The weapons suite reflects the transitional nature of early Clan engineering, mixing surplus SLDF equipment with newly developed Clan prototypes. The primary weapon is an Enhanced ER PPC mounted in the right arm, delivering punishing damage at extreme range. A Clan-specification ER large laser in the left arm provides a powerful secondary weapon, giving the Redback a devastating long-range alpha strike capability.</p><p>Close-range defense is handled by a pair of SLDF-surplus Inner Sphere medium pulse lasers, one mounted in the center torso and one in the head, retaining the accurate short-range firepower of the original Maelstrom design. A prototype Clan ER medium laser in the center torso extends the 'Mech's effective engagement envelope at intermediate distances. The retention of a TAG designator in the right torso preserves the artillery spotting capability that characterized the original Maelstrom. The combination of powerful Clan energy weapons with proven Star League systems creates a formidable brawler, though the experimental nature of several key components limited its widespread adoption even among the Widowmakers.</p>

deployment:<p>The sole configuration of the Redback mounts a weapons suite that reflects the experimental nature of early Clan weapons development. The Enhanced ER PPC and Clan ER large laser provide devastating long-range firepower that exceeds the original Maelstrom's capabilities, while the retention of SLDF-surplus Inner Sphere medium pulse lasers for close defense demonstrates the practical compromises necessary during this transitional era. The prototype ER medium laser adds a mid-range engagement option not found on the original design. No factory variants of the Redback are known to have been produced, as Clan Widowmaker's destruction in 2834 ended all further development of the design.</p>

history:<p>The Redback's history is inextricably linked to the tragic fate of Clan Widowmaker, one of the original twenty Clans founded by Nicholas Kerensky. Following Operation Klondike and the successful conquest of the Pentagon Worlds in 2821-2822, the Widowmakers turned their attention to improving the military hardware they had inherited from the SLDF. The Maelstrom chassis, with its proven Marauder-series lineage, was selected as the basis for one of their early upgrade programs, resulting in the Redback around 2828.</p><p>The design saw service with Widowmaker forces for only a brief period. Clan Widowmaker's increasingly erratic behavior and escalating conflicts with other Clans, particularly Clan Wolf, culminated in the Annihilation of Clan Widowmaker in 2834. Following the Widowmaker Absorption, Clan Wolf claimed the majority of Widowmaker assets, including their manufacturing facilities and remaining Redback chassis. The Dagda Industriplex Zeta, believed to have been the production site for the Redback, passed to Wolf control along with the rest of the Widowmaker industrial base.</p><p>Ownership of the facility eventually transferred to Clan Star Adder, who inherited the Dagda complex and its associated production capabilities. However, the Redback's mixed-technology design and reliance on prototype systems made it an unattractive candidate for continued production, and the facility shows no record of active Redback manufacturing under any of its successive owners. By the time Clan technology had fully matured, newer and more capable designs had rendered the Redback obsolete, leaving it as little more than a historical curiosity of the Golden Century.</p>

